manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: VIENON 7 in 1 USB A & C Hub Increase your productivity by expanding the female USB C port on your devices to multiple possibilities (1 x 60W PD, 5 x USB A data ports, 1 x USB C data port). With USB-A & USB-C male port, this hub is suitable for all laptops, desktops, and all-in-one computers on the market. All Ports could work simultaneously. One Hub to meet your daily use in work, home and travel.
Super-Speed Data Transfer Equipped with 5* USB 3.0 Ports, say goodbye to repeated plugging and unplugging to save your time and provide sleek workplace.

60W PD Charging Port USB C PD Charging allows you to charge your Laptop with a high speed pass-through charging up to 60W. Keep your Laptops on power all the time. USB C Data Transfer With 1 USB Type C data female port, it can connect to your type C phone for transferring files, photos etc. USB-A & USB-C Male Port Compatible with macbook, imac, and other lapotp/Tablet/desktop computer/all-in-one. Only one Hub is enough for all device, greatly saving purchase costs.

Wide Compatibility Comaptible with all Windows, Mac OS, Linux and Chrome system, all system versions are compatible. Independent Chip Each interface is equipped with independent chip management, ensuring that the 7 interfaces run simultaneously without interfering with each other. Aluminum Housing Hard aluminum alloy frosted shell, fingerprint resistant, scratch resistant, and fast heat dissipation. LED Indicator Light Equipped with soft blue LED indicator light, keeping track of the device's working status at all times.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars slick, compact, durable and functional
reviews.reviewText: This is my personal preference, but I like that the ports are only on one side and the end opposite the cord. This makes it much easier to manage the connection cords as they can lie flat and daisy chain them if even more than seven (7) total ports are needed. This device could make it very simple to create a Redundant Array of Inexpensive Devices (RAID) for a very secure backup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Totally great. Due to its accessories, it fits any computer and any holes in it. It also can receive any USB, narrow or wide, since it got holes for them all. It is a great gadget, and half the price of other, sophisticated gadgets like this. The only thing I wished it had, is if it "clicked" when you attach it to the computer so that you know it is done right. It does not make that click sound when attaching it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lots of ports for little $
reviews.reviewText: Good mix of the various types of USB ports to expand access to computers with too few ports. Inexpensive and it works.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Simple to use, plug and go
reviews.reviewText: This little device really packs a punch for travel, just plug it in to your laptop or mobile device and you got enough ports to do almost anything you would need. I'm using for travel and swapping SD cards. I like that the connection to my laptop offers an adapter for a standard USB or USB C type connection. Its super small and light weight making it a go to for travel and cafe' office at hotels and airports

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but perfectly formed
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 13 year-old who had been nagging me for a USB hub for ages. The cool thing about this is that it can work with either a USB-A or USB-C host computer. This is perfect for him because he has an old hand-me-down laptop which does not have USB-C, but his next laptop definitely will have.On the hub there are two USB-C connectors one of which can be used to give the hub power, if you are using it on a USB-A host.This thing is so much smaller than I thought it would be, and it will be perfect for those who travel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Charging port for laptop does not work
reviews.reviewText: I primarily purchased this so that I could charge my laptop on the rightside and not be tripping over it by converting the usb to the smaller usb and also have a port for my wireless mouse. It is not charging my laptop (the port that is supposed to charge) is not working. The charging port for the wireless mouse did work. I returned for a differen't brand.
